This was a great talk, and the number Paulo presented were impressive. Here are some notes I took during the session:
- One OutSystems customer went from <b>0 to 10K function points in 1 year </b>(they built 9 business apps equivalent to a small ERP);
- They delivered <b>172 release</b> (that 1 new release every 2 days) with an average of <b>232 Function Points per release</b>;
- <b>43% of the changes for those releases were related to database changes</b> (imagine the implications on the other layers, especially UI)
- With Model Driven Development, you basically transform <b>13M lines of code into ~3000 modeled elements</b>. This makes knowledge transfer between developers possible
